< review>
We had the whole house fan (Quiet Cool Stealth Pro 5.5x) installed recently by Atticare. They gave the best price/quote for the install and also the ones who could install right away. As we were going through a heat wave, we didn't want to wait for several weeks for the install.
The installation was quick. They did a clean job covering up everything including walls so that no dust would settle down anywhere. The whole installation took less than 2hrs.
The fan works great and we turn it on for an hour or two in the morning and also late evening to bring the house to outside temperature quickly.
The fan noise is minimal and you can barely hear it if you are >30ft away. It has a mild humming noise so not at all annoying. Our kids are able to sleep through it.
Overall we are happy with the fan and also the installation.<//review>

I hired Atticare to install a "whole-house" or attic fan by Quiet Cool. I considered giving them 2 stars, since the estimate, sale and installation process were smooth, but the actual poor result and lack of successful follow-up to mitigate it are so unsatisfactory that it outweighs that. In sum: I paid $1,600 and have a fan that does nothing. It turns on, but it does not cool the house, at all. When I reported this, they sent out someone who was extremely green, and who multiple times confidently said he'd discovered what was wrong, but it was clear that he didn't understand the most basic aspects of the installation, like the square footage of the house; he also didn't know how the fan worked or how to instruct me to use the fan. I was originally going to get attic insulation at the same time, but did not; one of the things this guy said was that it wouldn't work without insulation, which doesn't make sense, but if it is true, they should have told me that before installing the fan.

So either I got the wrong fan, they installed it incorrectly, they installed it in a non-ideal location for it to work well, or there is another factor or combination of factors (lack of attic vents? insulation? I'm not opening the right combination of windows/doors?). I have run many experiments myself to try to get it to work, to no avail.

Regardless, they have taken zero responsibility for the outcome of their work.</Text>

< review>
I really enjoyed interacting with the inspector who came out (Milo) and provided me his recommendation and quote. His feedback was reasonable and it was easy talking through options.

This is an expensive service- I paid $5500 for 1500 sq ft attic clean-up, rodent proofing and insulation replacement + crawl space clean-up.

Pros: The crew arrived on time, communicated arrival times in advance and did a good job of setting up the site.

Cons: The sub-contractor who came out to do the job tried to sell me a service on the side (insulating air vent pipes in the attic) claiming it was not covered and it would be cheaper if he did it on the side. I was blindsided since (a) I did not know why that service was not covered to begin with since I thought I opted for full recommended service or if that was omitted because it was not required in my case (and had to call the inspector to clarify) and (b) I do not appreciate the un-professionalism of side jobs and extra payments.

Also, I communicated to the crew-lead that there were 2 entrances to the crawl space and right after I showed him one he said they'd start with attic first. At the end of day when they said they are done with attic and crawl space I went on to check from both crawl space entry and found the area around the second no where near clean. On pointing out the crew mentioned that they must have not had access to this part from the other entrance- I would expect better knowledge and judgment or cross checking - they charged me for the whole space- if they could only clean half from one entry they should know to ask that something seems off. They did a quick job of trying to clean up but did not vacuum and also claimed that had run out of sanitizing liquids.

What I thought was full service was not nearly full service. Apparently cleaning the crawl space does not mean vacuuming. And insulating the attic does not involve insulating air ducts in there. Too many fine prints.

Overall expensive and much needed service but can be better. Has the same pitfalls as any contractor job that sub contracts.
‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶............

Update:

After I posted the above review the company contacted me and sent out a different sub contractor to finish up properly. This crew pulled out a huge amount of additional debris from my crawl space before they said they were done. I don't have a way to verify if this time indeed the work was left complete however I appreciate the company acting on feedback and making attempts to fix the problems from the first visit.<//review>

<Review>In April 2017 I requested bids from four attic clean-up companies to clean my attic. From the four offers I selected AttiCare. Their bid was very competitive and included all the items I wanted. They offered to remove all the old blown-in insulation, debris, and animal droppings; disinfect; seal all ceiling openings into the house; seal against rodent entry; cover any improperly installed pot lights; and install new R38 batting insulation.
AttiCare offered a number of dates from which to choose. They were scheduled to arrive between 9am and 11am. Juan Rosales arrived at 10am with his crew of three. They immediately set to work and had cleaned out the attic by 1pm. I inspected and found the work satisfactory and they then installed the new batting in about an hour. They were packed up and gone by 4pm.
I was very pleased with the timeliness and work performed by Juan Rosales and his crew.</Review></record>

<Time>1562625283424<//Time><Rate>5<//Rate><review>Once more, Atticare USA came through when we needed to address rodents in our home!  They are timely, professional, thorough and extremely fair in their pricing - particularly for all that they do.  In their recent visit, they took great care to prep the work site, as well as completely clean prior to leaving.  Their follow up, afterwards, was also comprehensive and prompt.  In the end, Atticare is clearly a company that wants to ensure their clients are completely satisfied with all aspects of what they do and for what they charge to do it.

I cannot recommend their work highly enough.  In the very least, if you have this kind of unfortunate circumstance, give them an opportunity to come out and provide a complete evaluation and quote.  They are not interested in "up-selling", and I have found them to be fair, honest and extremely reliabl

The entire experience from the initial call, meeting with Estimator Connor and the extremely professional team who did the work in our crawl space, Frandi, Kelmer and William was outstanding.  I obtained bids from a number of established, local businesses prior to choosing Atticare USA.  Not only was the bid from them considerably more competitive, but the approach was more thorough and I felt I was not being "upsold" with what they proposed.

They communicated well, were on time, and did not rush through the job.  Connor actually stopped by in person to ensure all was going well, and the team actually took many before and after photos and videos to ensure we felt all was completed to our satisfaction.  They also pledge in writing to stand behind their work, in the event something doesn't turn out as anticipated.

Bottom line - a crawl space cleanup is really unpleasant and, unfortunately, expensive.  My recommendation is that if you can avoid it by making sure your crawl space is secured, then great.  But.  If you have had a situation that necessitates the need to address it, Atticare USA, Connor and their experienced, polite, thorough and professional crew(s) is a great option all the way around. Let me just tell you...
This place is everything! All good and nothing bad.
I ordered the Carne Asada fries and this is my opinion on them:
-HUGE portions, extremely heavy. Definitely didn't skimp out on the meat.
-The taste was on point. No blandness whatsoever.
-The staff wasn't at all difficult like some. They catered to our request about having sour cream and guacamole in the side. Some places have issue with this for some reason.
-Extremely reasonable pricing. This giant order of Carne Asada fries was only $8.
-On top of everything else, they offer something they don't need to. They give 15% military discount as well. That alone makes me want to go back to support those who support us.

Anyway, I definitely recommend this place out. I'm glad I did and I'll be going back for sure whenever I'm on that side of town.</Review>

< Review>
We went here for the first time last night, and I'm so glad we did! My family loves sushi that highlights fresh raw fish, and we all enjoyed our rolls, and udon. With the funny, creative roll names, we had to first read thru all the descriptions (which were clearly written out on their website) of each roll, we ordered 5 and a veggie udon. Can't remember all, but there was an "Arigato", a "knocked up", "show me your love", "playboy"...and another.

When we drove up to Sky Sushi, we stayed in the car, called them that we were there, and they brought out the sushi.

As we drove home, I said "how are we supposed to remember which roll is which?". But to my surprise (and relief), each box was labeled with what roll was inside. What a wonderful detail they thoughtfully added to make our identification so much easier. I've never experienced that. Love it.

We received a good amount of wasabi, pickled ginger, soy sauce, napkins, and chopsticks, which is also a big plus! Friendly staff rounded out our 5-star first experience with Sky Sushi.

I just wanted to mention that the vegetable udon was also really good. It really hit the spot on a cold day!

We will be back for more!<//Review>

<Review>'20/2 1st time review, but customer for handful of years:
-- Located in a safe, older, tired Rancho Cordova strip mall that's well kept considering. Little transient presence.
-- While located on one of the busiest corners in Rancho Cordova and east Sacramento (Sunrise and Coloma), it does not inhibit easy in/out of strip mall--though peek rush hour requires navigating the heavily used three roads adjoining the mall.
-- For handicapped, there is parking, but will still be a walk to front door given location of restaurant in mall in relation to the designated handicap parking stalls.
-- Always a sandwich board outside and on the wall in small waiting area (see 3 pix posted). Well worth indulging, as chefs are culinary creators in taste and presentation.
-- Extensive drink/food menus and other specials (see pix uploaded for all).
-- Super impressed with dish/drink choices, visual presentation, and taste of food. Many different sauces, "bedding", toppings, and flavors impresses with each return trip.
-- Excellent, attentive wait staff. Kind, informative, helpful, and genuine--not pretentious.
-- Pickup counter is to the back of this small restaurant, and restroom past that.
-- Booth seating along south wall with table and sushi-bar counter seating taking up the rest of the floor space.
-- Did not see if offered booster chairs.
-- Yes, bathroom. Did not see quantity or if unisex.< /Review>< GmapID>

<rating>4<//rating>< Text>
Found this place on a recommendation of a acquaintance who suggested we try it. We dropped immid week in the late afternoon. A young chief was working the sushi bar counter. He welcomed us and asked what would we like to have. We ordered a couple of apetizer dishes from the kitchen and asked for white fish nigiri. He demurred, and offered sea bass which he suggested was good. It was. We moved on from there. Being sushi traditionalists we ordered all nigiri and a couple of temaki rolls. The fish was delicious, well prepared and beautifully presented. We have been back a few times and had semi omakase meals, which all turned out delicious. This is a real find. Chief Jay is thoughtful, careful in preparing each dish and recommending the best cuts. Truly a master of his craft, one of less than a handful in the Sacramento area. Highly recommended.</Text>
